== [[5:2 diet]] ==


RfC: [[Talk:5:2_diet#RfC:_What_should_the_opening_line_be.3F|Is 5:2 a 'fad diet'? Or just a 'diet'?]]

--[[User:Balaenoptera musculus|Balaenoptera musculus]] ([[User talk:Balaenoptera musculus|talk]]) 14:27, 20 May 2014 (UTC)

:It is whatever a reliable source says it is. It looks like a fad to me but I'm not reliable. [[User:Bhny|Bhny]] ([[User talk:Bhny|talk]]) 17:26, 20 May 2014 (UTC)
::The problem with "fad diet" is that it has quite a few meanings. Maybe a diet that enjoys temporary popularity, or maybe one which emphasizes only a certain foodstuff. It seemed fine to me to say the diet had been called a "fad diet" rather than asserting it (and this is well-sourced). But it's not worth the immense drama this question seems to have caused! [[User:Alexbrn|Alexbrn]] <sup>[[User talk:Alexbrn|talk]]|[[Special:Contributions/Alexbrn|contribs]]|[[User:Alexbrn#Conflict_of_interest_declaration|COI]]</sup> 17:32, 20 May 2014 (UTC)
 	
::Technically, are there any named diets that aren't, in some way or other, fad diets? It's not like there's any that have been consistently popular for decades. As such, I wouldn't consider the word useful. <span style="text-shadow:grey 0.118em 0.118em 0.118em; class=texhtml">'''[[User:Adam Cuerden|Adam Cuerden]]''' <sup>([[User talk:Adam Cuerden|talk]])</sup></span> 17:34, 20 May 2014 (UTC)

::: There are medically recommended diets and stupid fad diets, they are different things- [[http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/fad+diet]] [[User:Bhny|Bhny]] ([[User talk:Bhny|talk]]) 02:21, 21 May 2014 (UTC)

::[[User:Bhny|Bhny]], the issue (IIUC - and I haven't personally checked the sources) is that some but not all [[WP:RS]] call it a 'fad diet', so inclusion (or not) in the first sentence is a judgement of [[WP:WEIGHT]]. [[User:Balaenoptera musculus|Balaenoptera musculus]] ([[User talk:Balaenoptera musculus|talk]]) 09:18, 21 May 2014 (UTC)

::: It is a defined adjective in medical dictionaries [[http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/fad+diet]] that basically means not medically recommended. If the sources say it is a not  medically recommended (i.e. fad) then we should make this clear in the first paragraph.  There's strict policies on medical issues like diet. [[User:Bhny|Bhny]] ([[User talk:Bhny|talk]]) 14:12, 21 May 2014 (UTC)
